  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><style>[data-colorid=kljzl8r63w]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=kljzl8r63w]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=ywg18jne8l]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=ywg18jne8l]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=ndn8zy3358]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=ndn8zy3358]{color:#004eb3}[data-colorid=izfeu66ln0]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=izfeu66ln0]{color:#004eb3}</style><a href=\"/wiki/download/attachments/592019497/DemoSign_v01_h264.mov?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757511659022&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760\">DemoSign_v01_h264.mov</a></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Neon_Random1.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512680134&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=702\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/592019497/Neon_Random1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512680134&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"892\" data-width=\"965\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"592674820\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Neon_Random1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"592019497\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"3\" data-media-id=\"8a1b1eac-790c-4713-9004-c34e08c0e29a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512680134&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=965&amp;height=892 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512680134&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=702 1x\" /></span><p>Above is the Solaris scene graph for the randomization of all the lights in our scene. </p><p> All the magic happens inside <em>attributewrangle</em> nodes that control the lighting randomization of each letter in our sign.  I have one wrangle for each of the letters in the scene, as I want to have control over each letter individually.</p><p>Let&rsquo;s take a look at the meshlight Neon tubes first:</p><hr /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"ndn8zy3358\">Letters - D - M - O - Neon Tubes</span></strong></p><p>Create a <em>attributewrangle </em>node and under Primitives, we&rsquo;re selecting the neon tube meshlights we want this node to control. </p><p>Below is the VEX code used to set up the parameters</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"2ac86bbf-7a4a-4d16-9548-67d248508460\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">int off = chi(&quot;off&quot;);\nint on = chi(&quot;on&quot;);\nint transition = chi(&quot;transition&quot;);\nint A = off;\nint B = off + transition;\nint C = off + transition + on;\nint D = off + 2 * transition + on;\n\nfloat val = 0;\nint frame = int(@Frame - $FSTART + chi(&quot;frameOffset&quot;) * @elemnum) % (D + 1);\n\nif(frame &lt; A)\n    val = 0;\nelse if (frame &gt;= A &amp;&amp; frame &lt; B)\n    val = 1 - (B - frame) / float(B - A);\nelse if(frame &gt;= B &amp;&amp; frame &lt; C)\n    val = 1;\nelse if (frame &gt;= C &amp;&amp; frame &lt; D)\n    val = (D - frame) / float(D - C);\nval *= ch(&quot;intensity&quot;);\n\n@inputs:defaultFloat = val;\n//@inputs:intensity = val;</pre>\n</div></div><p /><p>We now have a set of parameters that will allow us to control the randomisation of the prims.</p><p><strong>OFF</strong></p><p>The number of frames that the neons are switched off.</p><p><strong>ON</strong></p><p>The number of frames that the neons are switched on.</p><p><strong>Transition</strong></p><p>The number of frames to transition between OFF and ON states</p><p><strong>FrameOffset</strong>: </p><p><strong>Intensity</strong></p><p>Sets and overrides the intensity of the lights</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Neon_Random2.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512946682&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=490\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/592019497/Neon_Random2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512946682&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"781\" data-width=\"1211\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"592904193\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Neon_Random2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"592019497\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"3\" data-media-id=\"d51fa3e2-8f8c-40ad-96e0-65a1d55f1474\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512946682&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1211&amp;height=781 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757512946682&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=490 1x\" /></span><p /><hr /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"izfeu66ln0\">Letter - E - Globe Bulbs</span></strong></p><p>This wrangler allows us to control the value of the two primvars we set up in the Globe bulb USD asset.  </p><p>Remember, these were called Bulb_COL and Bulb_INT</p><p>Here is the code</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"98915610-6170-4e6f-afc0-5bbe0823ced3\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">float randomFloat(float min; float  max; string primpath) {\n    return fit01(rand(random_shash(primpath), chi(&quot;seed&quot;)),min, max); \n}\n\n//@inputs:intensity = fit01(rand(random_shash(@primpath), chi(&quot;seed&quot;)), ch('min'),ch('max')); \n@inputs:defaultFloat = randomFloat(ch('min'),ch('max'), @primpath); \nfloat randomHue = randomFloat(ch('Hue'), ch('Hue'), @primpath + &quot;hue&quot;);\nfloat randomSat = randomFloat(ch('minSat'), ch('maxSat'), @primpath + &quot;sat&quot;);\nfloat randomVal = randomFloat(ch('minVal'), ch('maxVal'), @primpath + &quot;val&quot;);\nv@inputs:defaultColor = hsvtorgb(randomHue,randomSat,randomVal);</pre>\n</div></div><p>which creates this set of parameters</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Neon_Random3.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757513500360&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=519\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/592019497/Neon_Random3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757513500360&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"825\" data-width=\"1207\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"592838660\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Neon_Random3.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"592019497\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"3\" data-media-id=\"e3f9fc17-91bc-4b9d-bb1a-4de97a313347\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757513500360&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1207&amp;height=825 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757513500360&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=519 1x\" /></span><p><strong>Intensity Min + Max</strong></p><p>The min and max intensity values that will be randomly created for the bulb's intensity (Bulb_INT)</p><p><strong>Bulb Hue</strong></p><p>How much to randomize the hue of each bulb (Bulb_COL)</p><p><strong>Saturation Min + Max </strong></p><p> The minimum and maximum random saturation values of the bulb color (Bulb_COL)</p><p><strong>Value Min + Max</strong></p><p>The minimum and maximum random values of the bulb color (Bulb_COL)</p><p><strong>Seed</strong></p><p>Allows you to control the speed of the flashing of the bulbs.  </p><p>If left to a single frame, the bulbs will not animate. However, using the $FF expression causes the seed to change every frame, thereby animating the bulbs.</p><p><strong>Facing Ratio</strong></p><p>Allows you to control the facing ratio of the bulbs.</p><hr /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"ywg18jne8l\">Letter - S - Fairground Bulbs</span></strong></p><p>This wrangler allows us to control the intensity and color values of the tiny sphere light inside of the glass fairground bulbs.</p><p> </p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"bf9e628f-80cf-4b7a-b571-b496b93baf82\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">float randomFloat(float min; float  max; string primpath) {\n    return fit01(rand(random_shash(primpath), chi(&quot;seed&quot;)),min, max); \n}\n\n//@inputs:intensity = fit01(rand(random_shash(@primpath), chi(&quot;seed&quot;)), ch('min'),ch('max')); \n@inputs:intensity = randomFloat(ch('min'),ch('max'), @primpath); \nfloat randomHue = randomFloat(ch('Hue'), ch('Hue'), @primpath + &quot;hue&quot;);\nfloat randomSat = randomFloat(ch('minSat'), ch('maxSat'), @primpath + &quot;sat&quot;);\nfloat randomVal = randomFloat(ch('minVal'), ch('maxVal'), @primpath + &quot;val&quot;);\nv@inputs:color = hsvtorgb(randomHue,randomSat,randomVal);</pre>\n</div></div><p>Again, creating this set of parameters</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Neon_Random4.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757514400947&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=471\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/592019497/Neon_Random4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757514400947&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"753\" data-width=\"1214\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"592674831\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Neon_Random4.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"592019497\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"3\" data-media-id=\"baa045e7-468f-4f20-9066-23f1483fd19d\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757514400947&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1214&amp;height=753 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/592019497/Neon_Random4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757514400947&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=471 1x\" /></span><hr /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"kljzl8r63w\">Summary</span></strong></p><p>So &hellip; to summarize.</p><p>With this set of wrangles, we can randomly flash and control meshlights, the Glow intensity, and color of a PxrSurface and analytic USD lights.  </p><p>Feel free to use these code snippets in your scenes where you need to create randomisation of lights and shaders.</p>"
    }
  },
